I initally did this manually in cyberchef, performing the following steps:
1. Base32
2. Base64

Somehow after reaching the 3rd stage, cyberchef gives me a weird output that doesn't render properly on the screen (It was suppose to be Braille).

I ended up using a github tool called [ciphey](https://github.com/Ciphey/Ciphey) that automatically performs decryption/decoding/cracking tool using natural language processing & artificial intelligence. Feeding it my input, it was able to produce my flag in under *15 seconds* even though there were 5 rounds of encryption.
